//// github-slugger test suite (test/fixtures.json) so the anchors
//// produced here are exactly GitHub's. The fixtures are stateful:
//// they run in order through a single `Anchorer`, so repeated
//// headings exercise the duplicate counter.
////
//// The "Unassigned" fixture is omitted: it is built from codepoints
//// that were unassigned in Unicode 13 and have since been assigned,
//// so its expectations depend on the Unicode version of the regex
//// engine rather than on the algorithm.

